The paper discusses data mining techniques for social media analysis, which falls under the field of computational social science. The paper specifically focuses on social network data, which is a subcategory of social media. Therefore, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses information retrieval (IR) techniques for mining social media data, which makes cs.IR (Information Retrieval) another likely sub-category. The paper also mentions natural language processing (NLP) techniques for analyzing social media data, which falls under cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper discusses the challenges of analyzing social media data, which could fall under cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.DL (Digital Libraries).
